{
  "stem": "4830.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we went back to-- to this apartment house, which was an apartment house that was bombed and no longer suitable for tenants that this house, this military unit.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were there until we found that units-- other military units with fascist paraphernalia and armbands are surrounding these units and the area.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this man, whose name I don't remember, gave me the speech-- that if you want, we shall resist them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said our chances are nil, but at least we die for our country.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you decide.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they decided with a small majority that they'd rather survive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at which point, using the same escape routes that I always used to sneak in and out to my brother over the roofs of houses-- apartment houses-- I didn't want to surrender with my brother, so we escaped.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he came with me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I managed-- he didn't want to go, but I managed to convince him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were home when the fascists took over.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And third was a-- a-- really a final blow to the Jews of Budapest, because up until that time, they suffered very little losses.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But the fascists take over-- eliminated Governor Horthy, and a man who was probably insane, medically insane took over.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Colonel Szalasi, who became the supreme fascist leader of Hungary, and they started to deport the Jews of Budapest.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "As a first step, on October the 20th, they came to our-- no, the 18th-- they came to our apartment house that everybody from the age of 14 to 65 they will take away.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my younger brother was in that category.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So my mother was very upset.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they knocked on the door where I was hiding that they are taking Ervin.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
